  "prompt": "What are some movies, songs or books in which the characters have a non monogamous relationship (like polyamorous or a trouple)?",
  "response": "There's a growing number of movies, songs, and books that explore non-monogamous relationships such as polyamory or troupes. Here are some examples across different media:\n\nMovies:\n1. **\"Vicky Cristina Barcelona\" (2008)** - Directed by Woody Allen, this film involves complex romantic relationships including a polyamorous dynamic between the characters played by Javier Bardem, Pen\u00e9lope Cruz, and Scarlett Johansson.\n2. **\"Professor Marston and the Wonder Women\" (2017)** - This biographical drama explores the polyamorous relationship between Professor Marston, his wife, and their mistress, who inspired the creation of Wonder Woman.\n\nSongs:\n1. **\"She Keeps Me Warm\" by Mary Lambert** - Although not explicitly about polyamory, the song celebrates love and relationships in a way that can be interpreted as inclusive of non-monogamous dynamics.\n2. **\"Our House\" by Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young** - This song captures the spirit of communal living, which can sometimes include non-monogamous relationships.\n\nBooks:\n1. **\"The Ethical Slut\" by Dossie Easton and Janet W. Hardy** - Essential reading for anyone interested in understanding polyamorous relationships and ethical non-monogamy.\n2. **\"More Than Two: A Practical Guide to Ethical Polyamory\" by Franklin Veaux and Eve Rickert** - Another well-regarded resource offering insights and guidance on polyamory.\n3. **\"Stranger in a Strange Land\" by Robert A. Heinlein** - This science fiction novel features characters exploring non-monogamous relationships in a futuristic society.\n\nThese titles portray non-monogamous relationships in varied and interesting ways, offering perspectives that can enrich understanding of polyamory or trouples.",
